anat cohen quartet events at stanford anat cohen quartet facebook twitter email print add to calendar anat cohen's enthralling clarinet and saxophone artistry has dazzled the jazz world ever since she arrived on the new york scene just over ten years ago from her hometown of tel aviv via berkelee college in boston exploring and mastering multiple styles such as brazilian choro traditional jazz afro cuban tango klezmer and others earned her a reputation as an adventurous player unafraid to take risks in any situation with her own compositions and with even her affectionate tribute to benny goodman the king of swing her abandon is no less evident the boston globe reports the most interesting clarinetist of her generation she played with great physicality lurching thrusting blowing at length with eyes closed and head down but at the heart of her performance was a commitment to enjoy herself she had the audience in her palm when saturday july 2 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where campbell recital hall 541 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $40 general $30 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27943 more info last modified june 9 2011
